Definition: acting in a manner that is gentle and mild and even-tempered
Example: his fingers have learned gentleness; suddenly her gigantic power melted into softness for the baby; even in the pulpit there are moments when mildness of manner is not enough
Synonyms: adj, all, kind, gentle, soft, mild, light, softness, conciliatory, mildness, manner, acting, in, a, that, is, and, even-tempered, his, fingers, have, learned, suddenly, her, gigantic, power, melted, into, for, the, baby, even, pulpit, there, are, moments, when, of, not, enough
Category: noun.attribute
